Package: klue
Type: Package
Title: Hybrid ML and Random-Utility Workflow for Latent Class Model
    Specification
Version: 0.2.2
Authors@R: person("Oliver", "Frings",
                  email = "oliver.frings@agroparistech.fr",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Oliver Frings [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Oliver Frings <oliver.frings@agroparistech.fr>
Description: Implements the three-step workflow from Frings (2026, working
    paper) for specifying latent class multinomial logit (LCMNL) models:
    (1) initialise the maximum-likelihood multi-start from six clusterings
    of respondents' revealed-preference signatures (k-means, Gaussian
    mixture, three hierarchical methods, partitioning around medoids);
    (2) estimate LCMNL across a user-specified range of class counts;
    (3) benchmark against a mixed multinomial logit (MMNL) and report
    BIC, AIC, ICL, and a classification-entropy diagnostic alongside
    class-specific coefficients. Accepts any discrete-choice dataset in
    long or wide format, with optional availability columns and per-
    attribute scaling. Validated bit-exactly against five public
    reference datasets (Vittel water-quality discrete choice experiment,
    Apollo mode and route choice, Electricity, Swissmetro). Wraps the
    'apollo' package for the underlying maximum-likelihood estimation.
